		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: The best nes asm compiler?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I love ca65. Yes, there's a little bit of overhead to learn that you don't with NESASM (e.g. putting together an iNES header, setting up a .cfg file) but the power you get in return is well worth it, in my opinion.<br /><br />Not to mention that it comes with cc65, which is actually a real pain to set up, but now that I have it going full speed, it's just fantastic to be able to write C code instead of only assembly. Shiru has written a nice guide to this, and in the near future I plan to release some example source, myself. (I wrote my Famicompo entry this year mostly in C, which saved me a ton of time. I can't release it until voting is over though.)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


