		<td><b>Re: The best nes asm compiler?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I was just reading on Wikipedia about the 6502, and came across the screenshot of Terminator, where 6502 ASM code flashes across the Terminator's Vision.<br />It's a 1984 movie, and standard 6502 code looks exactly the same now as it did then, right down to the &gt; and &lt; operator to take the high and low byte of a 16-bit word.<br />But the code shown on the screen in Terminator wouldn't create identical output in NESASM as it would in any other assembler.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


